So in order for the points to
represent a function, for

00:00:09.140 --> 00:00:12.610
every input into our function,
we can only get one value.

00:00:12.610 --> 00:00:14.990
So if we look here, they've
graphed the point--it looks

00:00:14.990 --> 00:00:19.340
like negative 1, 3, so that's
the point negative 1, 3.

00:00:19.340 --> 00:00:23.740
So if we assume that this is our
x-axis and that is our f

00:00:23.740 --> 00:00:26.540
of x axis, and I'm just assuming
it's a function, I

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:29.320
don't know whether it really
is just now, this point is

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:32.820
telling us that if you put
negative 1 into our function,

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:34.760
or that thing that might be
a function, or maybe our

00:00:34.760 --> 00:00:38.520
relation, you'll get a 3 So
it's telling us that f of

00:00:38.520 --> 00:00:41.580
negative 1 is equal to 3.

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:43.220
So far it could be a reasonable
function.

00:00:43.220 --> 00:00:46.960
You give me negative 1 and
I will map it to 3.

00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:51.720
Then they have if x is 2, then
our value is negative 2.

00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.500
This is the point 2, negative
2, so that still seems

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:56.510
consistent with being
a function.

00:00:56.510 --> 00:01:01.170
If you pass me 2, I will map
you or I will point you to

00:01:01.170 --> 00:01:02.560
negative 2.

00:01:02.560 --> 00:01:03.930
Seems fair enough.

00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:05.230
Let's see this next
value here.

00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:09.250
This is the point 3 comma
2 right there.

00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:13.190
So once again, that says that,
look, if you give me 3 into my

00:01:13.190 --> 00:01:17.800
